Remove legacy config.py system - v1.0.0 migration complete

BREAKING CHANGE: PlotConfig class and related functions removed

This commit completes the v1.0.0 architecture migration by removing the legacy
config.py system that has been superseded by the modern PlotSpec implementation.

Changes:
- Archive config.py as config_legacy.py in _archive/ directory
- Remove PlotConfig import/export from __init__.py
- Remove config_from_file(), config_from_yaml(), validate_config() functions from api.py
- Remove unused yaml import from api.py
- Update plot() function to use PlotSpec.model_validate() for dict configs
- Clean package namespace - only PlotSpec remains for configuration

The v1.0.0 architecture is now complete with:
- PlotSpec: Modern Pydantic-based configuration with validation
- Standalone plotting functions: Clean separation of concerns
- Unified API: Single wv.plot() function for all use cases

All tests pass and package imports correctly. Test suite will be refactored
separately to use the new PlotSpec-based API. 